body:
Bumps [handlebars](https://github.com/wycats/handlebars.js) from 4.1.2 to 4.5.3.
Changelog *Sourced from [handlebars's changelog](https://github.com/wycats/handlebars.js/blob/master/release-notes.md).* > ## v4.5.3 - November 18th, 2019 > Bugfixes: > > - fix: add "no-prototype-builtins" eslint-rule and fix all occurences - f7f05d7 > - fix: add more properties required to be enumerable - 1988878 > > Chores / Build: > - fix: use !== 0 instead of != 0 - c02b05f > - add chai and dirty-chai and sinon, for cleaner test-assertions and spies, > deprecate old assertion-methods - 93e284e, 886ba86, 0817dad, 93516a0 > > Security: > > - The properties `__proto__`, `__defineGetter__`, `__defineSetter__` and `__lookupGetter__` > have been added to the list of "properties that must be enumerable". > If a property by that name is found and not enumerable on its parent, > it will silently evaluate to `undefined`. This is done in both the compiled template and the "lookup"-helper. > This will prevent new Remote-Code-Execution exploits that have been > published recently. > > Compatibility notes: > > - Due to the security-fixes. The semantics of the templates using > `__proto__`, `__defineGetter__`, `__defineSetter__` and `__lookupGetter__` in the respect that those expression now return > `undefined` rather than their actual value from the proto. > - The semantics have not changed in cases where the properties are enumerable, as in: > > ```js > { > __proto__: 'some string' > } > ``` > > - The change may be breaking in that respect, but we still only > increase the patch-version, because the incompatible use-cases > are not intended, undocumented and far less important than fixing > Remote-Code-Execution exploits on existing systems. > > > > [Commits](https://github.com/wycats/handlebars.js/compare/v4.5.2...v4.5.3) > > ## v4.5.2 - November 13th, 2019 > # Bugfixes > > - fix: use String(field) in lookup when checking for "constructor" - d541378 > - test: add fluent API for testing Handlebars - c2ac79c > > Compatibility notes: > - no incompatibility are to be expected > ... title: Fix name to github links at the bottom of the page
body: Name to github links at the bottom of the page are broken, need to fix

title: Get professor emails and northeastern page links
body: Replace dummy emails and northeastern page links for professor tiles with actual links/emails

title: Scrape Old TRACE
body: There is an old version of trace that we can use to get data back to 2011

title: Filter out Nonconstructive Comments
body: Use sentiment analysis to filter out nonconstructive and toxic comments

title: Replace metrics with straight aggregates
body: Remove metrics that combine multiple responses, and only include basic 1-response aggregates

title: Add documentation for user personas
body:
At HackDartmouth, we came up with four personas that a user may take on:

- Deciding DJ
- Certain Sauharda
- Time Sensitive Tal
- Regular Ryan

These should be documented.

title: Filter search results
body:
As deciding DJ, I want to be able to filter the classes to meet certain constraints (ex: math courses offered next semester with code # > 3000) so that I can easily find all classes for certain graduation requirements.

We might hook into the searchNEU api to get info on the upcoming semester.

Addendum:
This may also link into the degree audit parser, which could create a filter "only classes I haven't taken" and "only classes necessary for my degree" and "classes that help me graduate (nupath whatever)"

title: "Pin" search results
body:
As deciding DJ, I want to be able to "pin" search results so I can easily compare options for classes to take.

This might require having the search results cards expand to contain a bit more info? Also what if we want to compare "prof P teaching course C" versus "prof Q teaching course D?"

title: Make the profXcourse page
body:
There needs to be a page for specifically "how good is prof P at teaching course C"
It should have all the highlighted comments and overall ratings, but also every rating and comment in the surveys should be available. 

Questions:
Should we segment by year taught?
Any types of cool charts we could visualize for this?

title: Make the Professor page
body:
There's no professor page lol.
It should show:

- [ ] The courses the prof teaches, with a link to the profXcourse page

- [ ] Highlighted comments

- [ ] Overall ratings.

title: Show searchbar hint
body:
As a first-time user, I want to be shown what types of search terms I can search for, so that I can take full advantage of the search features.

This could be a little text thing that says "search for professors, courses names, or course numbers" or there could be an animation inside the search bar that "types" different sample search terms.

title: Make site mobile friendly
body:
Since this was programmed at a hackathon, I did not care in the slightest about responsive design. It's time to change that for the large amount of users who will probably want to search TRACE on their phones.

Planning on tackling this Monday, April 15.

title: Make SVG circles for professors show numerical scores inside them
body: Currently, on professor tabs, the circles are showing visual representations of the scores of the professors. This is cool, but we should also display the score itself, so that users of the site have some reassurance that what they're seeing is being backed by numbers.

title: Add custom hook for authentication
